Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - DB2/400 Incremental Update using CPYF native OS400 command. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled.
Restrictions : - All the mapped fields are updated during insert and update - The name of the target table must not be greater than 10 characters - The name of the flow table (I$) must not be greater than 10 characters - The update key can only be the primary key of the table. The update key of the Interface is ignored. - Does not work when loading read-only columns. - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore.
Uncheck this option if you do not want to insert / update data in the target table using CPYF
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface
Uncheck this option if you do not wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Check this option if you wish to empty the target table using CLRPFM command.
Set the Format Mapping. Can take any of these values : Specific values: *NONE, *NOCHK, *CVTSRC Other values : *MAP, *DROP, *CVTFLOAT, *NULLFLAGS

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%>, IND_UPDATE ) select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", ",", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <% if (snpRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> 'I' IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <%}%> from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=snpRef.getColList("", snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME] = I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand \t", "", "UK")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' )
